    "body": "When you load a `.js` file through a `<script>` tag it's embedded in the document, so\n\n```\n<body>\n  <h1>Electron Test</h1>\n  <script src=\"resource://js/main.js\"></script>\n</body>\n```\n\nis functionally equivalent to\n\n```\n<body>\n  <h1>Electron Test</h1>\n  <script>\n    const test = require('./test'); // Error: Cannot find module './test'\n    test.sayHello();\n  </script>\n</body>\n```\n\nWhich means that `./test` is resolved relative to `index.html`, not relative to `js/main.js`. To fix this you can do\n\n```\n<body>\n  <h1>Electron Test</h1>\n  <script>\n    require('../js/main.js');\n  </script>\n</body>\n```\n"
